715456f-a.text:
V. 126th (formerly Lawrence) Street, south side, east from a point midway betweenn Old Broadway and Amsterdam Avenue and towards the latter (extremme left and not seen). Shown is a vacant lot, a 4 story framme house, the Speyer School and several low structures. These buildings formerly were known as No's. 98 to 88 Lawrence Street but now bear No's. 518 to 498 W. 126th Street. St. Marys P.E. Church is on the side where the photographer is standing and therefor does not appear. In fact the vacant lot shown is directly opposite same.
April 1, 1938.
P.L. Sperr

715457f-a.text:
West 126th Street,(Lawrence) at the N.W. corner of Old Broadway. Also shown is Old Broadway, east side, north from West 126th Street, to and including 129th Street. View shows grounds and wards of the Sheltering Arms Home.
June 14, 1931.
P.L. Sperr.
No Reproductions.
